# SirHENRY Security Rules

## Zero-Knowledge Principles
- The service processes user data but does NOT retain it centrally
- Each user's SQLite database is their data — isolated, local, encrypted at rest
- Plaid access tokens MUST be encrypted with Fernet before storage (see `pipeline/db/encryption.py`)
- `PLAID_ENCRYPTION_KEY` is REQUIRED in production — fail fast if missing
- API keys (Anthropic, Plaid) live ONLY in `.env` — never hardcoded, never in DB

## Data Protection
- `data/` directory, all `*.db` files, `.env`, and `scripts/*.json` are gitignored
- NEVER log PII (names, account numbers, SSNs, balances, transaction descriptions)
- NEVER include financial data in error messages returned to the client
- NEVER store plaintext Plaid access tokens
- NEVER send user financial data to external services except Plaid (for sync) and Claude (for AI features)

## AI Data Handling
- Claude API calls include user financial context for the current request only
- Do NOT persist AI conversation history containing financial details outside the user's local DB
- System prompts must not instruct Claude to remember data across sessions

## CORS & Network
- Default CORS: localhost only (`127.0.0.1:3000`, `127.0.0.1:3001`, `localhost:3000`, `localhost:3001`)
- Production CORS must be restricted to the deployed frontend domain
- All API routes must use `Depends(get_session)` for DB access — no raw engine calls in routes

## Secrets Checklist
Before any commit, verify:
- No API keys in source files
- No `.env` values in committed code
- No hardcoded database paths with user data
- No Plaid tokens in logs or error responses
